scavengers x 3<br>
wallcrawler x 2<br>
cave troll x 3<br>
<br>
Moria Conditions:<br>
Plundered <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>ies<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(91)">They Are Coming</a><br>
goblin <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>y x 2<br>
Moria Events:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a> x 2<br>
<br>
Possessions:<br>
Scimitar x 3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(85)">Moria Axe</a><br>
cave troll hammer<br>
<br>
Sites:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(199)">Bag End</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(211)">Buckleberry Ferry</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(217)">Council Courtyard</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(224)">Mithril Mine</a><br>
Bridge<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(230)">Dimrill Dale</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a><br>
<br>
<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck is pure twilight control, plain and simple. Bid 0, and hope to go second so you can play buckleberry fields and avoid a skirmish at site 2. <br>
<br>
Often, in my fellowship turn, there is only 3 twilight by site 2 (i play a bounder, perhaps sting at site 1 and that&#39;s not enough to play anything, so i take the double move to 3 in turn 1. If your opponent can play anything, it&#39;s 1 measly minion that will give Frodo one or two wounds at most, then goes away. One caveat is if your opponent plays Nazgul, a witchking can rear its ugly head at site 3, so make sure you&#39;ve got at least 2 intuitions/stealths in your hand before moving to 3, or else use Thror&#39;s Map to play council courtyard.<br>
<br>
I guarantee, Frodo will do fine for himself until about site 5 or so, when site twilight really begins adding up. By this time, if you haven&#39;t overwhelmed your opponent (by clogging up his hand with unplayed minions, he should have a weaker than normal fellowship), things may start to get messy.<br>
<br>
Hopefully Boromir will be in your hand by site 6. It&#39;s time for damage control. It&#39;s OK if he gets things like blade tip or black breath, he&#39;s just there for life support until Aragorn comes out to lead Frodo out of danger at sites 8-9.<br>
<br>
Besides the site 1-3 jump, I would suggest against double moving because this not only endangers Frodo, but simply adds more twilight for your opponent to clear his minions with.<br>
<br>
Near the end, especially if Frodo is Blade Tipped, burdens can become an issue. Hopefully, extraordinary resistance, combined with the Gaffer, will remove them.<br>
<br>
If you see that you might beat your opponent to the end, start using bilbo to recycle those hobbit intuitions, which give +3 at the cost of 1 twilight.<br>
<br>
This deck most often wins by overwhelming its opponent at site 5, where a cave troll, keyward, runners with scimitars, scouts, and a nazgul typically come out.<br>
<br>
In the games I&#39;ve lost, I prematurely presume that my opponent, who is usually at site 6 (after single moving the whole game)and me at site 7, won&#39;t ever move twice, so I use bilbo to recycle a ton of shire cards back to my deck, thinking I will make it to the end in two turns.<br>
Thanks to a ranger&#39;s versatility, my opponents move from 6-8, and I only move from 7-8 and have to stop for fear of getting overwhelmed.<br>
At this point, I&#39;ve got a ton of shire in my hand and few minions, and my opponent will make it from 8-9 rather easily.<br>
<br>
In response to this, I added one copy of they are coming to my deck the other day, which will hopefully turn these shire cards into useful minions.<br>
<br>
Clearly, this deck is still going through some major changes, but has great potential, especially against the unprepared opponents.  I&#39;d love for others to try out this idea and to see what they come up with.<br>
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21632"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21632" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
